|WKBSYNTAX
======

|CKBengage
engage <npc>
engage <choice number>|WKB

DESCRIPTION
===========

|YKOEngage opens a dialogue with an NPC in your current room.

If the NPC has something to say, Darkflow will show the NPC's portrait,
dialogue, and any available choices. You can click a choice in Darkflow, or
use |CKBengage <choice number>|YKO from the command line.

If the NPC has no special dialogue configured, the dialogue window still opens
with a silent response and an option to disengage.

Using |CKBengage|YKO by itself works when there is only one NPC nearby that can
be engaged. If there are several, use |CKBengage <npc>|YKO instead.|WKB

EXAMPLES
========

|CKBengage crier
engage guard
engage 1|WKB

